content: The **Seletar Teleport** ([Chinese](/wiki/Chinese_language): 实里达卫星地面站; [Malay](/wiki/Malay_language): *Stesen Satelit Telekomunikasi Seletar*) is the third of four [satellite earth station](/wiki/Satellite_earth_station) in [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore) after the [Bukit Timah Satellite Earth Station](/wiki/Bukit_Timah_Satellite_Earth_Station) in [Bukit Timah](/wiki/Bukit_Timah), and the [Sentosa Satellite Earth Station](/wiki/Sentosa_Satellite_Earth_Station) in [Sentosa Island](/wiki/Sentosa_Island). It is located near [Lower Seletar Reservoir](/wiki/Lower_Seletar_Reservoir) in [Yio Chu Kang](/wiki/Yio_Chu_Kang), opposite [Seletar Expressway](/wiki/Seletar_Expressway) (SLE). This station is managed and owned by [SingTel](/wiki/SingTel). - [Singtel](/wiki/Singtel) - [Seletar](/wiki/Seletar) 1°23′50″N 103°50′03″E﻿ / ﻿1.3972°N 103.8343°E﻿ / 1.3972; 103.8343 This [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore) location article is a stub.
